      <div class="msgContentFrame">I believe they're useful for when you're switching to a casting job.  The casters have similar Pie-&gt;Dex, etc. traits. <br /> <br />Here's an example of how these Caster ones are useful to a Lancer: <br /> <br />Raising a stat such as Vitality via physical level points takes: <br />Vit 1-40 : 1 pt per +1 <br />Vit 41-80 : 2 pts per +1 <br />Vit 81-? : 3 pts per +1 <br /> <br />Now you're higher in rank, sitting at 100 base Vit, it'll take 15 of your bonus points to raise your Vit +5. <br /> <br />OR  <br /> <br />You rank up Conj and pick up: <br />Driven by Faith - Converts an attribute point allocation of Piety +5 into Vitality +5. <br /> <br />Now you can use 5 physical level points to raise your Pie by +5, which converts into +5 Vit. A savings of 10 pts =) <br /> <br />So pick up Dex-&gt;Int if you plan on playing a caster job later, if not save your money(guild marks)! (Yes there was an ING banner to the right while typing this)</div>
